cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for automatic retinal vessel segmentation using image processing techniques and supervised classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of probability distributions and likelihood functions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses morphological transforms, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of Bayesian classifier and GMM indicates that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
